<headline>Hard Freeze Warning issued January 13 at 4:57PM CST until January 14 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...HARD FREEZE WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST SUNDAY...
The National Weather Service in Shreveport has issued a Hard
Freeze Warning, which is in effect until noon CST Sunday.
* EVENT...An Arctic airmass will move into the region bringing
overnight low temperatures from around 5 degrees to 17 degrees.
* TIMING..Temperatures will quickly fall after sunset with hard
freeze conditions expected by mid to late evening and continuing
through midday Sunday.
* IMPACT...Crops and exposed vegetation will freeze. Exposed pipes
will also be prone to bursting.</description>
<instruction>A Hard Freeze Warning means sub-freezing temperatures are
imminent or highly likely. These conditions will kill crops and
other sensitive vegetation.</instruction>
